modules.description: This module provides functions to handle HTTP requests and responses within a RESTful application, including authentication, response generation, and routing. It operates on data types such as `www_authenticate`, `auth`, and tuples representing HTTP responses, working directly with Cohttp's request and response structures. Concrete use cases include implementing custom resource handlers, enforcing authentication challenges, and dispatching requests to appropriate resources based on URI paths.

This module provides functions to construct and manipulate request descriptors, enabling access to request headers, response headers, path information, and redirection flags. It works with Cohttp's request and header types, along with string-based path components and optional body values. Concrete use cases include extracting path parameters from RESTful routes, modifying request/response headers for middleware, and initiating HTTP redirects with proper location headers.

This module provides a set of operations for building and handling RESTful web services, including request routing, header manipulation, and response generation. It works with Cohttp's request and response types, string-based paths, and custom resource classes. Concrete use cases include implementing HTTP methods like GET and POST, setting response status codes and headers, and managing resource state across requests.
